Package com.tractrac.clientmodule.data

Classes that assist in receiving data for different (event) data types.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DataController.Listener
    Provides information on the status of live and stored data.
    DataController.TimeListener
    A callback that will be called when the UTC time of the live data server is received.
    ICallbackData<T extends Attachments,R extends TimeObject>  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CompetitorPositionOffsetData
    An instance of this class represents an offset position for a Competitor.
    CompetitorPositionRawData
    An instance of this class represents a raw (not snapped to a route) position for a Competitor.
    CompetitorPositionSnappedData
    An instance of this class represents a snapped position for a Competitor.
    ControlPointPositionData
    An instance of this class represents a position for a Control Point (or one of its two buoys/marks).
    DataController
    The main class for data subscription/retrieval.
    EventLocationData
    This class contains information about the location of an event, including the event URL and the database name.
    Helpers  
    MarkPassingsData
    Represents mark passings for a RaceCompetitor.
    MarkPassingsData.Entry
    Represents a control point with a corresponding time stamp for when the mark/control point was passed
    MessageData  
    Position
    Represents data for a GPS position
    RouteData
    Represents a route of a Race
    StartStopTimesData  
    TimeObject
